    <!-- Tutorial Pages -->
    <!-- Ringer priority tutorial page -->
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_title">Ringer Priorities</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_intro">When an event starts I\'ll try to find the most appropriate way to adjust your device\'s ringer.  By default I\'ll put the device in silent mode.  This can be changed in settings.  Preferences can also be set on a per-calendar and per-event basis.  Repeating events can share settings, or have different settings for each instance.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_continued">If an event has more than one setting, I\'ll use the one that\'s closest to the event instance.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_precedence">In order of increasing precedence I\'ll look for</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_calendar">A calendar specific ringer</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_series">An event series ringer</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_instance">An event instance ringer.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ringer_priority_final">If none of these are set, I\'ll use the default setting.</string>

    <!-- Welcome tutorial page -->
    <string name="tutorial_welcome_title">Welcome!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_welcome_intro">Tacere will automatically silence your device during calendar events.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_welcome_details">By default I\'ll silence your device\'s ringer for all events that are not all day events or are not marked as available within the calendar.  Silencing will begin 5 minutes before an event begins, and last 5 after the event ends.  I\'ll post a notification whenever an event starts.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_welcome_skip">If these defaults sound good, feel free to skip this tutorial, otherwise swipe over for more details on what can be configured.</string>

    <!-- Event list tutorial page -->
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_title">Event List</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_main_description">The main view shows a list of current and upcoming calendar events. By default I\'ll show events from all calendars for the next week.  Calendars can be selected, and the period shown can be adjusted within settings.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_item_description">Each item in the list represents a single event instance, so if an event repeats over multiple days I\'ll show a separate entry for each repetition.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_item_description_continued">Each entry in the list will display the event\'s title, the beginning  and end date and time, and the ringer that will be applied when the event becomes active.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_active_description">If an event is active its background will change color.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_list_future_description">Events that do not start today are dimmed slightly.</string>

    <!-- Ringer sources tutorial page -->
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_title">Event Ringers</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_default_description">The default ringer will be used if I can not find a more specific ringer for an event.  The default ringer can be changed in the settings.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_calendar_description">Calendar specific ringers can be set within settings.  If an event belongs to a calendar that has a ringer set, then that ringer will be used instead of the default.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_series_description">Repeating events can share a common ringer.  To set the ringer long press on any repeating event in the list and be sure to check \'Use for all repetitions of this event\'.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_instance_description">The instance specific ringer can be toggled by tapping on an event, or by long pressing on an event and choosing a specific ringer.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_event_ringers_ignore_description">By default I\'ll will ignore all day events and events that are marked as \'available\'.  These events will ignore the default and calendar specific ringers, but will silence if their event series or instance ringers have been set.</string>

    <!-- End tutorial page -->
